      "description": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) predictions from the subject CFD model were compared against an independent high-fidelity CFD reference solution generated using a separately validated solver (ANSYS Fluent with Giersiepen power-law damage model). Agreement within 8% across all 5 operating points was observed, supporting confidence in the hemolysis QoI. The activity team noted that the reference solution replicates the physical conditions of the FDA benchmark experiment and therefore serves as a proxy for experimental validation.",
