        "description": "A second CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2023R1) was configured with identical boundary conditions and geometry to the subject model. Steady-state RANS with SST k-omega turbulence closure and the Giersiepen hemolysis power-law were applied. Results were compared against the subject model output for RH at each of the 5 flow-speed operating points. No physical bench experiment or in-vitro hemolysis measurement was performed; the activity team argued that solver-to-solver agreement at this fidelity level is as informative as an experimental comparison for MRL 2.",
